[http://www.spice-3d.org Andreas Prlic] is Senior Scientist at the RCSB-PDB database in San Diego, California. Prior to this he worked as a PostDoc at the [http://www.sanger.ac.uk/ Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute], Cambridge, U.K.
Currently he is acting as project leader for BioJava. He developed the protein structure API. Other projects he was working on include e.g.  [http://www.efamily.org.uk/software/dasclients/spice SPICE] a browser for
protein sequence and structure annotations, based on the Distributed Annotation System.
